{"parse":{"title":"pepper","pageid":40930,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Pepper}}\n==English==\n[[Image:Pfeffer-Gewürz.jpg|thumb|right|Peppercorns (2).]]\n[[Image:Immature jalapeno capsicum annuum var annuum.jpeg|thumb|right|Peppers (capsicum).]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|piper||archaic}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|peper}}, {{m|enm|piper}}, from {{inh|en|ang|piper}}, from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*pipar}}, from {{der|en|la|piper}}, from an {{der|en|inc|-}} source; compare {{cog|sa|पिप्पलि||[[long pepper]]}}. The name was given to the capsicum fruit because of its unusual spicy taste, not unlike the Old World spice. Cognate with {{cog|sco|pepar}}, {{cog|stq|Pieper}}, {{cog|fy|piper}}, {{cog|nl|peper}}, {{cog|nds-de|Peper}}, {{cog|de|Pfeffer}}, {{cog|da|peber}}, {{cog|nb|pepper}}, {{cog|nn|pepar}}, {{cog|sv|peppar}}, {{cog|is|pipar}}.  {{doublet|en|falafel|peepul}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɛp.ə/|[ˈpʰɛp.ə]|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-pepper.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɛp.ɚ/|[ˈpʰɛp.ɚ]|[ˈpʰɛp.ɹ̩]|a=GA,CA}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛpə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|pep|per}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# A plant of the family {{taxfmt|Piperaceae|family}}.\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[spice]] prepared from the [[ferment]]ed, dried, unripe berries of this plant.\n# {{senseid|en|any of various Capsicum varieties; their fruit}} {{lb|en|UK|US|Ireland|and|Canada}} A fruit of the [[capsicum]] plant: red, green, yellow or white, hollow and containing seeds, and in a wide range of mild (sweet, nonspicy) to hot (spicy) varieties.\n#: {{syn|en|capsicum<id:any of various Capsicum varieties; their fruit>}}\n#: {{hypo|en|q1=mild/nonspicy|bell pepper|capsicum<id:any of various nonspicy Capsicum varieties; their fruit>|sweet pepper|;|q4=hot/spicy|chili#Noun|chili pepper|hot pepper}}\n# {{lb|en|baseball}} A game used by baseball players to warm up where fielders standing close to a batter rapidly return the batted ball to be hit again\n#: {{ux|en|Some ballparks have signs saying \"No '''pepper''' games\".}}\n# {{lb|en|cryptography}} A randomly-generated value that is added to another value (such as a password) prior to [[hash]]ing. Unlike a [[salt]], a new one is generated for each value and it is held separately from the value.\n# {{lb|en|boxing|slang}} A [[beating]]; a [[thrashing]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1906|author=Henry Downes Miles|title=Pugilistica|page=61\n|passage=He means to snatch the laurels from his brow, / At all his boasted pluck and prowess smile, / And give him '''pepper''' in superior style.}}\n#* {{RQ:Dickens Dombey and Son|passage=[T]he Chicken had been tapped, and bunged, and had received '''pepper''', and had been made groggy, and had come up piping, and had endured a complication of similar strange inconveniences, until he had been gone into and finished.}}\n# {{lb|en|MLE|slang}} A [[shotgun|shotgun]].\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2017-01-17|title=Kennington Where It Started|url=https://genius.com/Harlem-spartans-kennington-where-it-started-lyrics|lyricist=Biz of {{w|Harlem Spartans}}|note=[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ed-oXKDmca0&t=28 0:28]|passage=Chew beef like breakfast (Yum)<br/>Two shanks, get 'round in seconds (Two)<br/>Be feeding my area, '''peppers'''}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2023-06-18|title=100mph Freestyle x3|url=https://genius.com/Clavish-100mph-freestyle-x3-lyrics|lyricist=w:Clavish|note=[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VhQjuIqwoE8&t=204 3:24]|passage=Number plates already hot, and plus we've got like three '''peppers'''}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|Culpepper|overpepper|peppadew|pepperberry|pepperbox|pepperbush|pepperer|pepperette|peppergrass|pepperish|pepperless|pepperlike|peppernut|peppershaker|peppershrike|pepperwood|pepperwort|wallpepper|bell pepper\n|bepepper|Pepper X\n|green pepper|Ashanti pepper\n|pepperade|rattan pepper\n|pepper and salt|alligator pepper\n|peppercorn\n|peppering\n|pepperita\n|pepper mill,peppermill\n|peppermint\n|pepperpot|pepper disease\n|pepper shaker\n|peppertini\n|peppery\n|red pepper\n|Scotch bonnet pepper\n|sweet pepper|Ashanti pepper\n|white pepper\n|yellow pepper\n|black pepper|pepper vine\n|chili pepper|pepper-gingerbread|salt-and-pepper doris\n|hot pepper\n|malagueta pepper\n|pepper spray|salt and pepper chips|serrano pepper\n|salt and pepper|cone pepper|conic pepper|conical pepper|pepper weevil|sweet pepper\n|tabasco pepper|black pepper snake|Java pepper|pepper squash|pepper steak|poor man's pepper\n|banana pepper|betel pepper|bird pepper|Brazilian pepper tree|California pepper tree|cayenne pepper|cherry pepper|chile pepper|chilli pepper|Espelette pepper|ghost chili pepper|ghost pepper|Guinea pepper|Jamaica pepper|lemon pepper|mignonette pepper|monk's pepper|old man's pepper|pepper ball|pepper dulse|pepper gas|pepper gel|pepper Jack|pepper jelly|pepper nut|pepper pot|pepper roulette|pepper sauce|pepper tree|pepper-and-salt|pepper-gas|pepper-pot|pepper-spray|peter pepper|salt-and-pepper|Sichuan pepper|sport pepper|Szechuan pepper|tailed pepper|topepo|water pepper|Spanish pepper|pepper cake}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|tpi|pepa}}\n* {{desc|haw|pepa|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mh|pepa|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|plant}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|فِلْفِل|m}}, {{t+|ar|فُلْفُل|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|فلفل حراق|m-p|tr=felfel ḥaraʔ}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|բիբար}}, {{t+|hy|պղպեղ}}, {{t+|hy|տաքդեղ}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|জলকীয়া গছ}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|pimentera|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|bibər}}\n* Baluchi: {{t|bal|مرچ|tr=mirc}}, {{t|bal|پلپل|tr=pilpil}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|борос}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|пипе́р|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|pebrer|m}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᏗᏆᏲᏙᏗ}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|胡椒|tr=wu4 ziu1}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|胡椒|tr=hújiāo}}\n* Coptic: {{t|cop|ⲡⲓⲡⲉⲣ}}, {{t|cop|ⲁⲗⲃⲟⲩⲗⲃⲟⲩⲗ}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|biber}}\n* Erzya: {{t|myv|порцька}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|piprujo}}, {{t|eo|piproarbedo}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|pipar}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pippuri}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|poivri