{t|sh|па̏пар|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|bìber|m}}, {{t+|sh|pȁpar|m}}\n* Shan: {{t-needed|shn}}\n* Shona: {{t|sn|mhiripiri}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|pipi}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|korenie|n}}, {{t|sk|piepor|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|poper|m}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|peṕeŕ|m}}, {{t|dsb|per|m}}\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{t|hsb|popjeŕ|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|pimienta|f}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|pepre}}\n* Sundanese: {{t+|su|pedes}}\n* Swahili: {{t|sw|pilipili manga}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|peppar|c}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|мурч}}, {{t+|tg|филфил}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|மிளகு}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|борыч}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|మిరియము}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|พริกไทย}}\n* Thao: {{t|ssf|makámun}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t|ti|በርበረ}}\n* Tlingit: {{t|tli|si.áax'u at}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{t|tpi|pepa}}\n* Tonkawa: {{t|tqw|mummunchicew}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|karabiber}}, {{t+|tr|biber}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|ببر|tr=biber}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|burc}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|пе́рець|m}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|مِرْچ|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|مۇچ}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|qalampir}}, {{t+|uz|murch}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|pévaro}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|tiêu}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|pep}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|poeve|m}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|pupur|m}}, {{t|cy|bupur|m}}\n* Yakut: {{t|sah|биэрэс}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|פֿעפֿער|m}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ata}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|piilitsaaq}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|lwgmanh}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|upelepele}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|fruit of the capsicum}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|բիբար}}, {{t+|hy|պղպեղ}}, {{t+|hy|տաքդեղ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|bibər}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|борос}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|чу́шка|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|pebrot|m}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᏗᏆᏲᏙᏗ}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|番椒|tr=fân-chêu}}, {{t|hak|馦椒|tr=hiâm-chêu}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|菜椒|tr=càijiāo}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|pubren|f}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|biber}}\n* Danish: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t+|da|chili}}, {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|da|paprika}}\n* Dutch: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t+|nl|chilipeper}}\n* Esperanto: {{qualifier|mild}} {{t|eo|papriko}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|paprika}}\n* Finnish: {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|fi|paprika}}, {{qualifier|strong}} {{t+|fi|chili}}, {{t+|fi|chilipippuri}}\n* French: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t+|fr|piment|m}}, {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|fr|poivron|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|pemento|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|წიწაკა}}, {{t|ka|პილპილი}}\n* German: {{gloss|spicy}} [[Chili#German|Chili]], {{gloss|mild}} [[Paprika#German|Paprika]], {{t+|de|Paprikaschote|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πιπεριά|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|nīoi}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|פִּלְפֵּל|m|tr=pilpél}}, {{t+|he|פִּלְפֶּלֶת|f|tr=pilpélet}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|मिर्च|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|paprika}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|pipar|m}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|lada}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|piobar|m}}\n* Italian: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t+|it|peperoncino|m}}, {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|it|peperone|m}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|بیبەر}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|калемпир}}\n* Ladino: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t|lad|pimienton}}, {{qualifier|mild}} {{t|lad|pipirushka}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|capsicum|n}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|пиперка|f}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|lada}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|чинжүү}}\n* Nahuatl: {{t+|nah|chīlli}}, {{t+|nah|chilli}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|azeedíchʼííʼ}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|piment|m}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t|fa-ira|فِلْفِل}}\n* Polish: {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|pl|papryka|f}}, {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t|pl|papryka ostra|f}}, {{t+|pl|chili|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|pimento|m}}, {{t+|pt|pimentão|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|ardei|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|пе́рец|m}}, {{t|ru|болга́рский пе́рец|m|lit=Bulgarian pepper}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|па̀прика|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|pàprika|f}}\n* Seychellois Creole: {{t|crs|piman}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|paprika|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|pimiento|m}}, {{t+|es|chile|m}} {{qualifier| Costa Rica, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, México, Nicaragua}}, {{t+|es|ají|m}} {{qualifier| Dominican Republic}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|pilipili hoho}}\n* Swedish: {{qualifier|spicy}} {{t+|sv|chilipeppar|c}}, {{qualifier|mild}} {{t+|sv|paprika|c}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|మిరపకాయ}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|พริกหยวก}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{t|tpi|pepa}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|biber}}, {{t+|tr|paprika}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|bolgarskiy}}, {{t+|uz|qalampir}}\n* Wolof: {{t|wo|kaani}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|ikhanakhana}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+check|sh|pȁpar|m}}<!--Was in the section \"spice\" in which also ''biber'' is provided as Serbo-Croatian word-->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To add pepper to.\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To strike with something made up of small particles.\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cover with lots of (something made up of small things).\n#: {{ux|en|After the hailstorm, the beach was '''peppered''' with holes.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To add (something) at frequent intervals.\n#: {{ux|en|He liked to '''pepper''' long words throughout his conversation.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|slang}} To [[beat]] or [[thrash]]. <!--see John Camden Hotten's ''Slang Dictionary'' (1873)-->\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Romeo and Juliet|passage=I am '''pepperd''' for this world, I am sped yfaith, he hath made wormes meate of me}}\n# {{lb|en|cryptography}} To use a pepper {{gl|type of value used prior to hashing}}.\n# {{lb|en|transitive|MLE|slang}} To [[shoot]] (upon) with the [[dotty]].\n# {{lb|en|transitive|slang}} To write [[accent]]s or [[disambiguate|disambiguating]] [[marks]] in [[script]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n*{{l|en|pepper up}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|add pepper to}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|պղպեղել}}, {{t|hy|[[պղպեղ]] [[ավելացնել]]}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|pubra}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|pebre}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pippuroida}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|poivrer}}, {{t|fr|[[assaisonner]] [[de]] [[poivre]]}}\n* German: {{t+|de|pfeffern}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πιπερώνω}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|borsoz}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t-needed|hrx}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|pipra}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|pepare}}, {{t|it|[[condire]] [[con]] [[pepe]]}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|pefferen}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|забиберува}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|попровац}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|pieprzyć}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|apimentar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|pipera}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|перчи́ть|impf}}, {{t+|ru|поперчи́ть|pf}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|okoreniť}}, {{t|sk|koreniť}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|popoprati}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|peppra}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|biberlemek}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|poevrer}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|strike with small particles}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|поръсвам}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|suolata}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|salpicar}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|acribillar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|peppra}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|cover with lots of small things}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|recouvrir}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|salpicar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|add at frequent intervals}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|համեմել}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|höystää}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|ponctuer}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|peppra}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|salt}}\n* [[w:Pepper|Wikipedia article on pepper]]\n* [[w:Capsicum|Wikipedia article on peppers (fruits of the capsicum plant)]]\n\n{{topics|en|Peppers|Piperales order plants|Seasonings|Spices}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|peper}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n{{wp|no:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nb|non|piparr}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{rfp|nb}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nb|noun|g=m|definite singular|pepperen}}\n\n# {{l|en|pepper}} {{q|spice}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nb|pepperkake}}\n* {{l|nb|peppermynte}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l-nn|pepar}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n{{C|nb|Spices and herbs}}"}}